Use the wavefunctions and energies of the hydrogen atom to determine the
 ground and excited state energies of hydrogenic systems.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Describe models of bonding, including ionic, covalent, metallic, and Van
 der Waals, using quantum mechanical concepts of energy minimization.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Calculate the specific heat for fermions (e.g.
 electrons) and bosons (e.g.
 phonons) in 1, 2, and 3 dimensions, given the density of states.
 
\end_layout

